Built with AngularJS!

Dependencies (tested in Ubuntu 12.04):

$ sudo add-apt-repository ppa:chris-lea/node.js
$ sudo apt-get update
$ sudo apt-get install nodejs build-essential # Yep, you're going to need make, gcc, etc...
$ sudo npm install -g grunt-cli

Build instructions (in /plugins/arDrmcPlugin/frontend):

$ npm install
$ grunt build
$ php symfony cc # In root directory

You can run "grunt watch" to detect changes during development and trigger the build.
Take into account that "grunt build" will be still necessary to be executed once when
you are configuring a new environment or the vendor browserify build has changed. See
Gruntfile.js for more details.

Mock REST API server instructions:

The mock REST API server usually runs on port 2403. The dashboard is available at /dashboard.

Installation:
$ sudo apt-get install mongodb
$ sudo npm install -g deployd
$ cd mock_api
$ npm install

Run:
$ ./start_mock_api

POST sample data to API:
$ ./mock_api/populate_sample_data <TCP port of API server>

Rewrite AIP sample data (example):
$ curl http://127.0.0.1:2406/aips-raw | python -mjson.tool > mock_api/sample_data/aips.json

Have nginx substitute mock API for real API:

Alter /etc/nginx/sites-available/default to include:

  location /api/ {
    rewrite  ^/api/(.*) /$1 break;
    proxy_pass http://localhost:2405/;
  }

  location /index.php/api/ {
    rewrite ^/index.php/api/(.*) /$1 break;
    proxy_pass http://localhost:2403/;
  }

...and change the FastCGI location criteria to:

  location ~ ^/(index|qubit_dev)\.php(/!(api)|$) {
